People have done it.  The internal combustion engine is not an effecient use
of gasoline.  Only about 18% of the gasoline's potential energy is being
utilized.  The rest is thermal energy, heat, burning our valves and going
right out the tailpipe.  The hydrogen booster system, as mentioned may only be
30% effective.  But it's more effecient than gas...
